reviews.comments: love it

reviews.headline: Mascara is clumpy.
reviews.comments: I was so excited to try this at the suggestion of a sales clerk. But got it home and the first time was really good. The 3rd and 4th time were clumpy messes. I tried cleaning off the wand but to no avail. I'm taking back and trying something cheaper.

reviews.headline: Tarantula lashes!!
reviews.comments: I really wanted to love this mascara but it's horrible! My lashes clumped together and looked like spider legs! Way too pricey a hard pass for me!

reviews.headline: Nope. Smudge City.
reviews.comments: I have never had so many problems with a mascara smudging. I wear minimal make-up and my skin is well moisturized. I feel like powder might help against the smudge city but if you generally rock a fresh-face minimalist make-up approach, basic drug store mascara will stay longer for far cheaper.

reviews.headline: Didn't see much improvement in length
reviews.comments: This is not a bad product, but for the price, I'm sure there are less expensive alternatives. I personally didn't see much improvement to the length of my lashes, but the coverage was great and I love MAC, so I will likely buy again.

reviews.headline: Absolutely my favorite mascara
reviews.comments: Stays on. Doesn't smudge. Eyelashes looked separated and long.

reviews.headline: Takes a few tries
reviews.comments: The first few times I wore this mascara I had issues: clumps, smudges, and "raccoon eyes". Each time, I tried a little something to help. I found some success. I also have had dozens of compliments. If I cry, it doesn't run. It doesn't smudge. Not even the tissue I use to dab my eyes has traces of mascara. And I've ugly cried. I thought I bought waterproof. Nope. Unfortunately this incredible staying power is hard to remove. The more oil the better.

reviews.headline: If Superstack is too clumpy, Try Micro!
reviews.comments: At first I got the regular black Superstack mascara but it just felt so heavy and clumpy no matter what I did. I decided to try the Micro stack and wow what a difference! Even though I have long lashes, I guess they're just thin and/or sparse. With the Mico brush, it doesn't clump and I can keep reapplying without it turning into spider lashes. I still get as much volume and length as I want for any occasion, just less clump. It stays on during the day and I haven't noticed any flaking or melting onto my lids. It washes off easy with my cleansing balm. So, if you're having too much mess from the Superstack, try the Micro!

reviews.headline: Love the bruah!
reviews.comments: Love the brush. Mascara goes on smooth. But It does flake a lot after being on about 6 hours

reviews.headline: No I won't buy again.
reviews.comments: It was not what I was expecting after all the hype about it on the Internet. I didn't like it at all, it leaves lots of clumps.

reviews.headline: smudges on the face

reviews.headline: I would buy this product again!  Much better than L'Oreal.
reviews.comments: This mascara is so much better than L'Oreal telescopic!

reviews.headline: From Sample to Staple
reviews.comments: I received this as part of a GWP and had never heard of the mascara or tried it before. I've tried so many different brands over the years and I have to say this mascara really shocked me with how much I love it. I have used it as my daily mascara for several months now and I will definitely purchase it once my sample runs out!

reviews.headline: TERRIBLE RACCON EYES
reviews.comments: Don't buy this unless you want two black eyes

reviews.headline: Heavy formula
reviews.comments: Love the way this looks when first applied; it is beautiful. Lifting, lengthening, and volume! However after an hour your lashes will fall. Even with curling and cool setting. I believe it is due to the formula being heavy. It also flakes a bit but I don't have an issue with transfer. For the price I just don't think I would buy it again. I like the initial application better than any mascara I have used but for length of wear the HighSky is way better and under $15.

reviews.headline: Formula to heavy
reviews.comments: I wanted to love this however the formula seems to heavy making my lashes loose its shape quickly. Disappointing

reviews.headline: my new favorite
reviews.comments: i got this mascara as a xmas gift and ive already pretty much used up the mini tube, and will be purchasing my own full size. this mascara has made me put down the falsies because i get beautiful lashes everytime with this mascara. the brush can be a bit abrasive so be careful, but i really like it bc i can pack on the mascara for volume, as well as use the brush to separate lash clumps to maximize fullness. i have naturally long lashes as it is but i really like the push up and curl hold i get with this as well. i definitely reccommend giving this a shot!

reviews.headline: 4th tube!
reviews.comments: This stuff is AMAZING. It goes on perfectly. Dont even have to try to wiggle it in your lashes or anything. Its stackable like it says without being clumpy! Im literally on like my 4th tube since this came out a few years back.

faceoff_positive.comments:
Hello my lovely readers! I was recently gifted the new MACStack Micro Brush Mascara by Bzzagent in exchange for a review.

The MACStack Micro Brush Mascara retails for about $28, and claims that it's clump resistant, layerable, separates and defines lashes, is nonflaking, and lasts up to 24 hours. So let's see if it stacks up to these claims.

Let's get this out of the way, mascara is not a makeup product I invest a lot of money into, nor is it part of my daily wear routine. I wear glasses most of the time, and mascara has the tendency to stick to the lenses while it's drying. I tend to wear mascara more for formal events, or when I'm wearing contacts. I've tried a lot of mascaras: Maybelline, Thrive Causemetics, Ipsy, Benefit, and Tarte.

Like most mascara MACStack has that distinct aroma that is reminiscent of ink. As a fragrance enthusiast, I found it quite abrasive. Compared to other mascaras, that aroma is definitely louder. Most of the time I don't even notice it. Another great thing about the MACStack also dries fast, like within a few seconds. Some mascara formulas can take up to 30 seconds to dry. Compared to other mascaras, MACStack was very difficult to remove. It needed a few rinses with an oil cleanser, and I had to actually scrub my lashes.

The bottle itself is quite stylish. It definitely screams Mac, with the black and sleek design. However it fits very comfortably in the hand, and the metallic ball in the handle is a great usability feature, it makes opening the bottle comfortable and fast.  Some other mascaras I have tried feel very uncomfortable and stiff in your hands. I also liked that the bottle stands by itself. Sure, nearly all mascara bottles aside from the more quirky shaped bottles can stand upward on your vanity. But living in a state prone to earthquakes, I was quite amused that it maintained its position longer than other mascaras when I shook the desk< /p>

But let's move on to the actual product. I really enjoyed the application process. Even with a hand that is less experienced than my fellow makeup wearers who religiously wear mascara, the mascara looks nice, not very clumpy, or spiderlike. It applied very evenly, which is sometimes an issue I have with other mascara. When you don't wear mascara as often, you can sometimes botch up the application by applying too much, especially with more straight and stiffer wands. But even with three coats the lashes just look darker and smooth.

I also quite enjoyed that the color was very apparent in one application. With two swipes the lashes were distinctly longer. My lashes with mascara are usually a smidge shorter. It's not a difference that is big enough to be discernible by others but trying a few formulas was noticeable to me.

The brush is quite nice. Straighter brushes are useful for applying color. , but I've always preferred more curved brushes because they are more in sync with the natural curve of your eyelashes. Curved brushes also help in avoiding clumpy eyelashes. I was quite happy to use the curved brush. It also is quite efficient in allowing me to focus on certain areas of my eyelashes, without immediately covering everything.I liked that I could shape my eyelashes a little better. The pigment is quite nice, my eyelashes match the color of my dark brown hair, and it's not too black that it looks like printer ink.

Upon pressing my fingers onto the mascara, the texture is clearly dried mascara, but it's not as stiff as other formulas which I quite enjoy.

THE CLAIMS:

So what about its claims about being clump resistant, layerable, separates and defining lashes, nonflaking, and lasts up to 24 hours?

It is definitely clump resistant. The mascara did not pill or clump. I was able to apply three layers and it did not look stiff or cakey. The lash separation seemed to perform pretty similarly to other mascaras I tried. I did not really see a difference between this mascara and another mascara in regards to the separation of lashes. As for its non-flaking claims, I didn't notice any flakes. But formulas in the $20 typically do not flake. As for its 24 hours claim, I got a good 15 hours wear out of it. But let's be honest, the average makeup consumer is not going to wear makeup for 24 hours. I certainly was not going to sleep in mascara to test the claims. But it is long-lasting, and would definitely last the whole day. .< /p>

Overall I quite enjoyed wearing the MACStack. The MACStack k formula is quite good. I can't deny it. The mascara looks wonderful, the pigmentation is nice. I absolutely adore that it's not clumpy. MACStack is quite long-lasting. When I initially applied at 7:00 am on my first day, it lasted until 10PM and didn't need any touch-ups. I found it actually a bit tedious to remove because it adhered so tightly to my lashes. Overall Mas has hit it out of the park with MACStack. It's a cute little mascara that I think would be enjoyed by mascara enthusiasts.

I would feel very confident in recommending this to my cousin who absolutely adores mascara and is a daily wearer, and equally to my Tita who enjoys brands that you would find in the Department store or Sephora

While I enjoyed the MACStack, I must be honest. I know personally, I would never spend $28 on mascara. Mac has solid formulas, and the mascara performs phenomenally. It is definitely worth your money. But I cannot justify spending $28 on a product that will get minimal use in my makeup toolkit, especially when I've enjoyed formulas from drug stores for under $12 and other formulas priced around $24. I would much rather experiment with a couple of colorful mascaras than spend it on an effective but highly common black mascara.

Should you purchase it?

You should if you're interested in a lengthening mascara, have difficulty applying mascara, or enjoy Mac's catalog. But I think I will not be repurchasing.

faceoff_negative.comments:
For me, I don't know if I will be repurchasing this mascara. I have used it twice since receiving it and while the brand is great and I really like the color, this mascara is not a great fit for me. It is a very wet mascara, and stays wet for a while. I have the traditional very straight Asian eyelashes that struggle to hold a curl, so most of the time I wear waterproof mascara. After curling my eyelashes and applying 1 layer of mascara, my eyelashes were the same length, no more curl, and the mascara was already smudging. I did recurl and then reapply (twice) for the final result that I have included in the picture. The length did increase in comparison to the other eye, but much effort and curling was put into the final product.

In addition, there was a difficult time separating the lashes with the wand itself -- potentially because it was new and there was a good amount of product on the wand. In terms of the wand itself, it's a pretty cool wand -- it gradually gets smaller at the tip and has hard ridges to help not clumping. 

However, throughout the day, my mascara did smudge under my eyes, and didn't stay. In addition, it eventually lost its curl. I use a different mascara usually and I think I will stick with that. 

I did receive this mascara in exchange for a review.
faceoff_negative.headline: Can see the advantages, but not for me
